cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper discusses the effectiveness of peer production model across the rural/urban divide, which involves social systems and human-computer interaction (HCI) aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also involves data analysis and modeling, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses challenges in characterizing rural phenomena, which could be relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
